NORTHWEST OHIO WIND, LLC RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Northwest Ohio Wind, LLC ("Northwest Ohio") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Northwest Ohio wind generating facility ("Northwest Ohio Facility").
The Northwest Ohio Facility is a merchant wind turbine generating facility located in Paulding County, Ohio. The Northwest Ohio Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by AEP Ohio Transmission Company and under the operational control of PJM Interconnection, LLC ("PJM").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Northwest Ohio's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Northwest Ohio Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Northwest Ohio's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Northwest Ohio shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $540,000.00
The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $540,000.00/12 = $45,000.00.
